import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    species_count = data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts()
    species_count.plot(kind='bar', color='green')
    plt.xlabel('Wildlife Species')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wildlife species involved in aircraft incidents?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    aircraft_make_model = data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(aircraft_make_model.index, aircraft_make_model.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Aircraft Make and Model')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Incidents')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of aircraft makes and models involved in incidents?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Effect_Amount_of_damage'])
    plt.hist(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Effect Amount of Damage')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the effect amount of damage caused by wildlife strikes?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Phase_of_flight'])
    phase_of_flight_counts = data['Phase_of_flight'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(phase_of_flight_counts.index, phase_of_flight_counts.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Phase of Flight')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of the phase of flight during which incidents occur?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Cost_Total__'])]
    plt.hist(data['Cost_Total__'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['Cost_Total__'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["Cost_Total__"].median():0.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Total Cost')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the total cost of incidents?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
